State moves to delete the penalty enhancer on count 1.   Motion granted.   
Count 1 - Deliver Schedule II Narcotic - No contest plea.   Convicted.   State moves to dismiss and read in count 2, deliver schedule II narcotics within 1,000 feet of school as repeater.  Motion granted.  Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.   Conditions of probation are:
1) Pay $200.00 for buy money to Metro Drug Unit from bail;
2) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
3) Maintain absolute sobriety except from prescriptions legally prescribed to her and taken in prescribed doses;
4) Pay costs of action; 
5) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
6) Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge;
7) One (1) year jail; Six (6) months, up front under the Huber Law, to commence on 12-31-15 by 6:00 p.m.; Six (6) months jail, stayed, to be imposed upon the agent's discretion.   
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights. 
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.  
Voter Ineligibility Notice and Acknowledgment.   
Minutes.
